-- AIG to securitize $5 bln-$10 bln: report
-- 
-- Sun Mar 1, 2009 3:38pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/03/01/us-aig-brief-idUSTRE52028X20090301

 

 (Reuters) - American International Group is to securitize $5 billion-$10 billion in debt, backed with life insurance 

 assets, to reduce debt burden under revised U.S. government bailout plan, the Wall Street journal said on Sunday. * Following securitization, transfer of equity stakes in alico, aia units to government, $60 billion fed credit facility for AIG to be reduced to $25 billion-WSJ * Transfer of equity stakes in alico, aia overseas units to U.S. government to repay much of $40 billion fed loan: WSJ